The bundle contains the exact upstream repository tree renamed to
herdr-0.7.4, including Cargo.lock, Cargo.toml, build.rs, and upstream's
vendored patched portable-pty and libghostty-vt code. It also contains the
locked Rust registry and Git dependency sources under vendor/cargo, all 36
package-source directories named by libghostty-vt/build.zig.zon.json under
vendor/zig-global-cache/p, a relative .cargo/config.toml, and
OPENHARNESS-CORRESPONDING-SOURCE.md. Open Harness creates it with Cargo 1.96.1,
Zig 0.15.2, and Python 3. Generated Zig local caches and build outputs are
excluded; legitimate upstream and fetched executable modes and symlinks are
preserved.

This corresponding source is intended to permit a conservative rebuild; Open
Harness does not claim that rebuilding it produces a byte-identical executable.

